      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Consider customizing how your spells look when you can cast them. You might wield your Prismari spells with dynamic, gestural movement-as much dance as somatic component. Even a blast of fire in your hands is a sculpted work of art; elemental forces make grand designs as you hurl spells. These forces might linger on your body or in your clothes as decorative elements after your spells are dissipated, as sparks dance in your hair and your touch leaves tracings of frost on whatever you touch."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "h1",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building a Prismari Character"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Any class or subclass that wields elemental forces of cold, fire, lightning, and wind can be a good fit in Prismari. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Druids"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sorcerers"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are common in Prismari, and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Wizards"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " who study the Schools of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Evocation"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Transmutation"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are also well represented. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Clerics"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " aren't very common in this school, but some with the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tempest Domain"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " end up here."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beyond the ranks of traditional spellcasters, Prismari students also include "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monks"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " who follow the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Way of the Four Elements"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Some acrobatic "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rogues"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fighters"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (including those who emulate the archetype of the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eldritch Knight"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") also delight in the athleticism of Prismari performance."
          }
        ]
      },
